=3D"text-align:justify">X.509 is a digital certificate that is built on top=
 of a widely trusted standard known as ITU or International Telecommunicati=
on Union X.509 standard, in which the format of PKI certificates is defined=
. X.509 digital certificate is a certificate-based authentication security =
framework that can be used for providing secure transaction processing and =
private information. These are primarily used for handling the security and=
 identity in computer networking and internet-based communications.</p><h3 =
style=3D"text-align:justify"><strong>Working of X.509 Authentication Servic=
e Certificate:</strong></h3><p style=3D"text-align:justify">The core of the=
 X.509 authentication service is the public key certificate connected to ea=
ch user. These user certificates are assumed to be produced by some trusted=
 certification authority and positioned in the directory by the user or the=
 certified authority. These directory servers are only used for providing a=
n effortless reachable location for all users so that they can acquire cert=
ificates. X.509 standard is built on an IDL known as ASN.1. With the help o=
f Abstract Syntax Notation, the X.509 certificate format uses an associated=
 public and private key pair for encrypting and decrypting a message.</p><p=
 style=3D"text-align:justify">Once an X.509 certificate is provided to a us=
er by the certified authority, that certificate is attached to it like an i=
dentity card. The chances of someone stealing it or losing it are less, unl=
ike other unsecured passwords. With the help of this analogy, it is easier =
to imagine how this authentication works: the certificate is basically pres=
ented like an identity at the resource that requires authentication.</p><p>=
<img src=3D"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/202203031310=
50/X509AuthenticationServiceCertificateWorking.jpg" width=3D"800" alt=3D"Wo=
rking of X.509 Authentication Service Certificate"></p><h3 style=3D"text-al=
ign:justify"><strong>Format of X.509 Authentication Service Certificate:</s=
trong></h3><p><img src=3D"https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/upload=
s/20220303131123/X509AuthenticationServiceCertificate.jpg" width=3D"800" al=
t=3D"X.509 Authentication Service Certificate Format"></p><p style=3D"text-=
align:justify">Generally, the certificate includes the elements given below=
:</p><ul><li style=3D"text-align:justify"><strong>Version number:</strong> =
It defines the X.509 version that concerns the certificate.</li><li style=
=3D"text-align:justify"><strong>Serial number:</strong> It is the unique nu=
mber that the certified authority issues.</li><li style=3D"text-align:justi=
fy"><strong>Signature Algorithm Identifier:</strong> This is the algorithm =
that is used for signing the certificate.</li><li style=3D"text-align:justi=
fy"><strong>Issuer name:</strong> Tells about the X.500 name of the certifi=
ed authority which signed and created the certificate.</li><li style=3D"tex=
t-align:justify"><strong>Period of Validity: </strong>It defines the period=
 for which the certificate is valid.</li><li style=3D"text-align:justify"><=
strong>Subject Name:</strong> Tells about the name of the user to whom this=
 certificate has been issued.</li><li style=3D"text-align:justify"><strong>=
Subject=E2=80=99s public key information:</strong> &nbsp;It defines the sub=
ject=E2=80=99s public key along with an identifier of the algorithm for whi=
ch this key is supposed to be used.</li><li style=3D"text-align:justify"><s=
trong>Extension block:</strong> This field contains additional standard inf=
ormation.</li><li style=3D"text-align:justify"><strong>Signature: </strong>=
This field contains the hash code of all other fields which is encrypted by=
 the certified authority private key.</li></ul><h3 style=3D"text-align:just=
ify"><strong>Applications of X.509 Authentication Service Certificate:</str=
ong></h3><p style=3D"text-align:justify">Many protocols depend on X.509 and=
 it has many applications, some of them are given below:</p><ul><li style=
=3D"text-align:justify">Document signing and Digital signature</li><li styl=
e=3D"text-align:justify">Web server security with the help of Transport Lay=
er Security (TLS)/Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) &nbsp;certificates</li><li sty=
le=3D"text-align:justify">Email certificates</li><li style=3D"text-align:ju=
stify">Code signing</li><li style=3D"text-align:justify">Secure Shell Proto=
col (SSH) keys</li><li style=3D"text-align:justify">Digital Identities</li>=
</ul><div class=3D"textBasedMannualAds_2"><p><a href=3D"https://practice.ge=
